{
  "texts": [
    "Comparison of the design process between different design methods.",
    "Conventional methods in the design stage require drawing 2D plans, creating 3D models, applying materials to the models, and rendering visualizations.",
    "In contrast, our method only requires textual descriptions to generate design visualizations directly.",
    "In the modification stage, conventional methods require repeating the entire design process, while our method only requires modifying the textual prompts to regenerate the design.",
    "We employed a state-of-the-art aesthetic scoring model 49 for the automated aesthetic annotation of interior design images."
  ]
}